### Hello, my name is

# Stephen Salerno

I am a postdoctoral fellow in Biostatistics at the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center, working with Jeff Leek. I received my PhD and MS in Biostatistics from the University of Michigan under the supervision of Yi Li, and a BS in Biometry and Statistics (with a minor in Health Policy) from Cornell University.  

My research focuses on:

- Statistical methods for drawing inference on algorithmically derived variables (post-prediction inference)  
- Deep learning for high-dimensional data  
- Survival analysis and causal questions in oncology and chronic disease  

I also work on clinical quality measures, public reporting, and health policy — especially in kidney disease and lung cancer — and I’m committed to building user-friendly software and contributing to data-for-good initiatives.

